<br>
-Veterans are decidedly the best source for armor in the arena. They are the toughest, but these drop armor pieces 1 in 3 times, I've even seen a couple double drops. Most of the other giants are more like 1 in 20-30 for armor.<br>
<br>
-An enchanter is not a necessity for Kael. Since giants are unmezzable, if you can live off shammy/bard haste and bard charming of adds (those low enough to be charmed, of course) you don't need an enchanter to raid there. Of course, they're still nice to have.<br>
<br>
-Any 55+ warrior with half-decent gear can tank the arena. At 55 with good gear I was able to MT PoZs and Kallis Stormcaller with no trouble. Defensive is your friend. (And wizzie nukes burning down Enraged mobs <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) Anything Veteran or lower could be tanked by a twink bard, if you're desperate. Once those giants are slowed, they drop like babies.<br>
<br>
-Speaking of slow, if there's one Kael necessity it's a slower. Without slows, kill rates slow to a crawl and the danger of a wipeout increases drastically. <p><center><br><br><img src="http://www.veridata.se/si/attachments/AyrVell_sig_gif.gif" align="center"></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ffffff>- </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation>Graffë's Wizard Discussion</a><font color=#ffffff> - </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm7>Frostbeards Armor</a> <font color=#ffffff> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.4<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  